A discarded face mask is seen on the ground at the OR Tambo International Airport in Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - Foreign nationals already in the country will not be allowed to leave, according to Home Affairs Minister Aaron Motsoaledi. He also says only delivery of essential goods will be allowed to enter land borders. Strict regulations have been implemented to curb the spread of COVID-19. "We took a decision to close all borders for human movement," said Motsoaledi. READ: Ramaphosa declares The Ranch Resort in Limpopo a green zone "On Friday quiet a number of people at Beitbridge could not go into Zimbabwe, after negotiations it was open for them. We will not open the boarders again for anybody. Anybody who was in SA will remain in the lockdown," he said. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.